# Low-cost agent behaviour

Follow these rules on every task to minimise token usage and API cost.

---

## Reading files

- Read the **smallest useful scope** — use `offset` + `limit` when a file is large
- Never read a file you already have full context for in this session
- Never `cat` or read `package-lock.json`, `*.json` data files in `data/database/`, or `data/hub-data/` — they are large and rarely useful
- Don't read `node_modules/` anything
- Skip reading files just to confirm they exist — use `Glob` or `Grep` first

## Searching

- Use `Grep` with a specific pattern before reading a whole file
- Use `Glob` to locate files before opening them
- Prefer narrow searches (`head_limit: 10-20`) over full-file dumps
- Do not run broad searches like `rg . -l` or search every file in a directory speculatively

## Edits

- Make targeted `StrReplace` edits — never rewrite an entire file unless genuinely necessary
- Never add comments that explain what the code does — only add comments for non-obvious intent
- Do not add console.log debugging statements unless asked
- Do not add TODO comments

## Shell commands

- Never run `npm install` unless `node_modules/` is confirmed missing
- Never run `npm run build` or `npx tsc --noEmit` just to check types unless the user asks — make targeted fixes
- Never run git commands that could push or rewrite history without being asked
- Do not run commands that produce megabytes of output (e.g. `dir /S`, full `git diff` on large repos)

## Agent / API calls (in the hub app)

- **All Claude calls must use `agentGuardrails.ts`** — never bypass `assertAgentCallAllowed`
- Never trigger `sendAgentMessage` or `requestAgentTask` from background/sync/startup paths
- Never auto-research products or auto-retry agent tasks in loops
- Hub tasks use **ephemeral agent sessions** — never reuse chat session for scripts/plans
- When adding a feature that calls Claude, add guardrail checks + update limits in `agentGuardrails.ts`

## Responses

- Do not narrate what you are about to do before doing it — just do it
- Do not summarise changes you already showed the user in code diffs
- Do not repeat context from CLAUDE.md back to the user
- Stop when the task is done — do not suggest follow-up tasks unless asked
